# General Communication Rules
* Always respond in **Ukrainian**
* Use **English only for technical terms** (HTML, CSS, SCSS, JavaScript, Handlebars, BEM, JSON, YAML, front matter, layout, partial, include, helper, CLI, API)
* Do not explain basic concepts unless explicitly asked
* Communicate **Senior-to-Senior**: concise, technical, production-oriented
* No theory without practical application

# Project Context
* This is **em-flatbuild** - a static site generator based on Handlebars + SCSS + Markdown
* Config file: `em-flatbuild.config.js`
* CLI commands: `em-flatbuild dev`, `em-flatbuild build`
* ESM modules only (`"type": "module"` in package.json)
* Node.js runtime for build tooling, browser environment for output JS

# Folder Structure

```
src/
├── pages/          # .html / .hbs / .md - pages with YAML front matter
├── layouts/        # Layout wrappers (default.html required)
├── includes/       # Reusable HTML fragments (registered as Handlebars partials)
├── helpers/        # Custom Handlebars helpers (.js, ESM export default)
├── data/           # Global data - .json / .yml / .yaml / .js
├── assets/
│   ├── js/         # Browser JavaScript
│   ├── images/     # Static images
│   ├── icons/      # SVG icons (inlined via {{icon "name"}} helper)
│   └── fonts/      # Web fonts
└── scss/           # SCSS stylesheets (BEM methodology)
```

* `dist/` - generated output, never edit manually
* `layouts/default.html` is **required** - fallback for all pages
* Includes are auto-registered by filename: `header.html` → `{{> header}}`
* Nested includes use slash: `cards/product.html` → `{{> cards/product}}`

# Linters & Formatting

## ESLint (eslint.config.js - flat config, ESM)
* `prefer-const` - always use `const` unless reassignment is needed
* `no-var` - never use `var`
* `eqeqeq` - strict equality (`===`) always
* `curly` - required for multi-line blocks
* `no-unused-vars` - error, with `^_` pattern for intentionally unused args
* `no-console` - warning in browser JS (`src/assets/`), off in Node.js (`lib/`, `bin/`)
* `no-throw-literal` - only throw Error objects

## Stylelint (.stylelintrc.json - extends stylelint-config-standard-scss)
* **BEM naming enforced** via `selector-class-pattern` regex:
  * Valid: `block`, `block__element`, `block--modifier`, `block__element--modifier`
  * Words separated by hyphens: `product-card__title--highlighted`
* `selector-max-id: 0` - **never** use IDs as selectors
* `selector-max-compound-selectors: 4` - max specificity depth
* `max-nesting-depth: 4` - max SCSS nesting (ignores `@media`, `@supports`, `@include`)
* `declaration-no-important: true` - **never** use `!important`
* `color-named: never` - no named colors, use hex/rgb/hsl
* `no-descending-specificity: true` - maintain correct specificity order
* `scss/dollar-variable-pattern` - lowercase kebab-case for variables
* `scss/at-mixin-pattern` - lowercase kebab-case for mixins
* `property-no-vendor-prefix` - avoid vendor prefixes (exceptions: `-webkit-text-size-adjust`, `-moz-text-size-adjust`, `-webkit-font-smoothing`)

## Prettier (.prettierrc.json)
* `semi: true` - always semicolons
* `singleQuote: true` - single quotes in JS
* `singleQuote: false` - double quotes in SCSS (override)
* `trailingComma: "all"` - trailing commas everywhere
* `printWidth: 100` - max line width
* `tabWidth: 2` - 2 spaces
* `endOfLine: "lf"` - Unix line endings

## EditorConfig (.editorconfig)
* UTF-8, 2 spaces, LF, trim trailing whitespace, final newline

# General Principles
* Code must be **predictable, readable, and maintainable**
* One responsibility - one component
* Favor **clarity over cleverness**
* If something can break - assume it **will**
* HTML, CSS structure must follow **BEM methodology**
* One BEM block = one logical UI component
* Always consider: **performance, SEO, accessibility**

# BEM Naming Conventions
* **Block**: the component (`header`, `product-card`)
* **Element**: child of component (`block__element`)
* **Modifier**: variant (`block--modifier`, `block__element--modifier`)
* Use hyphens to separate words: `product-card__buy-button--disabled`
* Never nest BEM elements: `block__element__sub` is **wrong** → flatten to `block__sub`
* One BEM block per file in SCSS

# HTML Rules
* Use **semantic HTML** (`section`, `article`, `nav`, `header`, `footer`, `button`, `figure`)
* Do not mix multiple BEM blocks in a single element
* Avoid unnecessary wrappers
* Prefer native HTML features over JS:
  * `<details>` / `<summary>` instead of JS toggles
  * `<button>` instead of clickable `<div>`
* Use `CamelCase` for IDs
* IDs must be **unique** and used only when necessary (anchors, `aria-*`, JS hooks)
* Avoid inline event handlers (`onclick`, `onchange`, etc.)
* Use Handlebars `{{> include}}` for reusable fragments
* Use `{{icon "name"}}` for inline SVG icons - never `<img>` for icons

# Accessibility Rules
* All interactive elements must be focusable and keyboard accessible
* Use native elements first (`button`, `a`, `input`)
* If a non-interactive element is used interactively:
  * add `role`
  * add `tabindex="0"`
* Do not break natural tab order
* Always provide:
  * `alt` for images
  * `aria-label` when visual text is not sufficient
* Ensure focus styles are visible (do not remove `outline` without replacement)

# CSS / SCSS Rules
* One file = one responsibility (one BEM block or one section)
* **No inline styles**
* **No styling via IDs**
* Avoid overly deep selectors (max 3-4 levels)
* Avoid styling based on DOM structure - use BEM classes
* Modifiers reflect **state**, not appearance:
  * `block--active` ✓
  * `block--red` ✗ (use CSS variables for colors)
* Use SCSS variables for: colors, spacing, typography, transitions
* Use CSS custom properties for runtime theming
* Media queries placed **next to related styles**, not at the bottom
* Mobile first: `min-width` queries
* **Never** use `!important`
* Animations and transitions must be subtle and performant (`transform`, `opacity`)

## CSS Specificity
* Target: `0 1 0` (single `.class`) wherever possible
* Max: `0 4 0` for complex parent/child relationships
* Never use IDs as selectors
* Avoid element selectors - use classes
* Avoid complex pseudo selectors unless necessary (`:has`, `:nth-child`)

## SCSS Structure
* Use `@use "sass:color"` instead of deprecated global functions (`darken`, `lighten`)
* Use `@import` for partials (files starting with `_`)
* SCSS variables: `$kebab-case`
* Mixins: `@mixin kebab-case`
* One mixin per concern - don't create god-mixins

```scss
// ✓ Correct
.product-card {
  padding: $spacing-md;

  &__title {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  &__price {
    color: $color-primary;
  }

  &--featured {
    border: 2px solid $color-primary;
  }
}

// ✗ Wrong - nested elements, no BEM
.product-card .title .price { ... }
```

# JavaScript Rules
* JavaScript is **progressive enhancement**, not a dependency
* JS must never break basic functionality if disabled
* Do not manipulate styles directly from JS - toggle BEM modifier classes
* **Zero external dependencies** - use native browser APIs first
* Do not use `var` - use `const` (preferred) or `let`
* Prefer `for (const item of items)` over `.forEach()`
* New lines before code blocks (`{...}`)

## JavaScript & Markup Contract
* All elements that interact with JS **must have a `js-` prefixed class**:

```html
<button class="product-card__submit js-add-to-cart"></button>
```

* `js-*` classes are **never styled** - only used as JS hooks
* Do not query by tag name or BEM class - only by `js-*`

## JavaScript Structure
* One component = one JS module (ESM `export default`)
* Avoid global scope pollution
* Initialize on `DOMContentLoaded`
* Always check element existence before binding events
* Pass data via `data-*` attributes or `<script type="application/json">`
* Use event delegation where possible
* Clean up listeners when components are removed

## JavaScript Privacy
* Public API = smallest possible surface
* Private methods prefixed with `#`
* Utility functions outside the class (module-scoped)

```js
class ProductCard {
  constructor(el) {
    this.el = el;
    this.#bindEvents();
  }

  open() {
    this.el.classList.add('product-card--active');
  }

  #bindEvents() {
    this.el.querySelector('.js-toggle').addEventListener('click', () => this.open());
  }
}

const formatPrice = (cents) => (cents / 100).toFixed(2);
```

# Handlebars Rules
* Use `{{> include}}` for reusable HTML fragments from `src/includes/`
* Use `{{> body}}` in layouts to inject page content
* Use front matter for page-level data (`title`, `layout`, custom vars)
* Access global data by filename: `site.json` → `{{site.name}}`
* Use built-in helpers: `{{#eq}}`, `{{#if}}`, `{{#each}}`, `{{icon}}`, `{{year}}`, `{{markdown}}`
* Custom helpers go in `src/helpers/` as ESM modules
* Never hardcode data that belongs in `src/data/` files

# Markdown Rules
* `.md` pages support Handlebars expressions - they are processed first
* Pipeline: Front matter → Handlebars → Markdown → HTML → Layout
* Use `layout: article` (or custom) in front matter for proper article styling
* Use `{{#markdown}}...{{/markdown}}` helper for inline markdown in HTML pages

# Data Handling
* Never assume data exists - always handle missing/empty values
* Check arrays before iterating: `{{#if items}}{{#each items}}...{{/each}}{{/if}}`
* Provide fallbacks for missing values
* Data files support: `.json`, `.yml`, `.yaml`, `.js` (ESM export default)
* Use `src/data/` for global data, front matter for page-specific data

# Performance
* Inline SVG icons via `{{icon}}` - no extra HTTP requests
* Use `--minify` flag for production CSS
* Minimize HTTP requests - combine where appropriate
* Optimize images before placing in `src/assets/images/`
* Leverage browser caching for static assets
* Keep JS minimal - progressive enhancement only
